6 pillars of Data Quality
What ?
Why ?
How ?
What is Data Quality?
Data Quality is the process of making sure data is fit for consumption and meets needs of consumers.

What is Data Quality Management?
The Planning, Implementation and control activities that apply quality management Techniques

Benefits of Data Quality ? Why?
Accurate Decision Making 
Improved Operational Efficiency
Enhanced Customer Experience
Better Analytics and Insights
Compliance and Risk Mitigation 
Cost Savings
Trust and Reputation 

Data Quality Process Explained
Discover - Define  - Integrate - Monitor
Discover:
Profile Data to understand anomalies in data sources 
Define:
Define cleansing and standardization rules
Integrate:
Deploy defined rules into data quality processes
Monitor:
Continuously monitor and report on data quality 

How is Data Quality Measured? 
6 Pillars of Data Quality
Accuracy : Data reprsents "reality"
Validity : Data conforms to expected format, type, range 
Completeness : All the data required for a particular use is present and can be used 
Uniqueness : Data appears only once in a dataset
Timeliness : Data is available when expected and needed 
Consistency : Data values should not conflict with other values across the dataset 
